    "name": "Rozen Maiden: Zuruckspulen",
    "link": "/series/Rozen%20Maiden%3A%20Zuruckspulen",
    "release": "04/Jul/2013",
    "desc": "Rozen Maiden: Zuruckspulen - During the events of the original Rozen Maiden, after circling \"yes\" on a paper and agreeing to wind an unknown \"something,\" a traumatized Jun Sakurada fights alongside the lifelike dolls known as the Rozen Maidens. But what would have happened if Jun had circled \"no\"?<br>\nJun, having gotten over his school trauma from his younger days, spends his time attending college and working in a bookstore. However, he does not feel as though he belongs anywhere. One day, he finds a book containing instructions on how to make a Rozen Maiden. Mysteriously, when he arrives home that night, the second volume in the book series has been delivered to his house, along with some pieces of a doll. But as suddenly as they started arriving, the books stop coming, and Jun gets a notice that says that the books have ceased being published. With an incomplete doll in hand, and a message from his other self in another world, this Jun also finds his way into the world of the Rozen Maidens.",
